dcterms:description: A benchmark dataset for few-shot learning, consisting of images from the ImageNet dataset split into training, validation, and test sets. It is commonly used to evaluate few-shot learning algorithms.
dcterms:title: miniImageNet

dcterms:description: A dataset derived from ImageNet, designed for few-shot learning tasks. It contains more classes than miniImageNet and is split into training, validation, and test sets, with a focus on evaluating models on unseen classes.
dcterms:title: tieredImageNet
